  "excerpt": "New Tom Ford Lip Color Lipstick + Lip Pencils. A look at the new reformulated lip products from Tom Ford Beauty.",
  "siteName": "The Beauty Look Book",
  "favicon": "",
  "text": "Tom Ford reformulated a few of their lip products for the Lip Color Lipstick ($62 each) + Lip Pencils ($46). It seems a number of items are going through a revamp as it appears the Foundation Stick has been pulled (or not restocked) along with a few other items. I hauled quite a few of the new shades and am 10/10 happy with everything I picked out. It has been a while since I’ve repurchased a Tom Ford lipstick and have to say I am shocked at the prices these days. I don’t know that luxury makeup is “worth” the steep price tags that keep increasing, but I have been really pleased with the performance, quality and colors with this particular haul. If you missed out on the Sephora sale, keep an eye out for upcoming holiday sales. A lot of retailers offer a good discount (flash sale) or gift card events and with Cyber Week approaching I’m sure you will be able to find these at a lower price. Lip Color Lipstick Tom Ford Beauty Lip Colors have been reformulated and with nearly every single brand revamping or repackaging I suppose it was only a matter of time before Tom Ford followed. The new formula has a little more slip to it. It glides on the lips better, isn’t quite as opaque, has a tiny bit of shine but still has great color payoff. I think the new formula is a noticeable improvement for a more modern look. The original was a classic for sure but because some of the colors were so opaque (especially the pale ones) they ended up looking a little too heavy. The new formula looks a little more natural on the lips while still being a true classic lipstick formula. These still have the same classic soft vanilla scent and mahogany + gold packaging (which I love). I am a bit sad they didn’t keep all the shades though. Shades I hauled below: Spanish Pink is a nude pink, it’s more wearable and a bit warmer than the original Sable Smoke is still the same flattering beige nude I remember (unfortunately I don’t have the original anymore to compare) West Coast is a 90s kind of brown cinnamon sepia shade Slip is a blue-based baby pink Runway Rose is a plum pink rose Casablanca is a mauve pink, the new one seems to have less grey undertone and I can actually wear the new version (the original one made me look a little ashy) Impassioned is a pretty reddish plum, it’s almost identical to the original, I could barely tell the difference between the two variations I ordered mine sight unseen and was lucky every single color works for me! Lasting power is just like the original formula and stays put for hours but fades nicely/evenly. These are a solid win for me. Lip Pencil Tom Ford revamped their Lip Pencil and the formula is exceptionally good. It’s everything I want in a lip liner! Formula is smooth, creamy, opaque, doesn’t look too dry on the lips and stays on the lips really well. They’re not completely budge-proof but they adhere well to the lips. I do miss some of the shades in the older formula (ones with the brush) but the four I picked are stunning. The colors I bought are all variations of a neutral tone. 101 Close-Up is a nude pink 102 Re-See is a light beige 103 Irresistible is a tan brown 106 A-List is the perfect brown tone Overall some solid wins even though I’m not too happy about the ridiculously steep prices. Quality is 10/10 and they launched some really beautiful classic colors that you can apply without any fuss or tweaking. I picked mine up from Sephora and Nordstrom. Available at all Tom Ford Beauty counters now.",
